news.title: Turning Noida into metropolitan council will need change in law
news.para: The Supreme Court has asked the Uttar Pradesh government to consider replacing the Noida Authority. The replacement would be with a metropolitan council for better governance. This direction follows a report highlighting issues like centralized decision-making and lack of transparency. The court has ordered immediate actions. These include appointing a vigilance officer and forming a citizen advisory board.

news.title: Mahindra looks to acquire 350-acre land parcel in Igatpuri
news.para: Mahindra & Mahindra has expressed interest in acquiring 350 acres in Igatpuri, Maharashtra, to potentially establish a supplier park or expand facilities for its Nashik and Igatpuri plants, according to Executive Director Rajesh Jejurikar. CEO Nalinikanth Gollagunta also revealed plans to increase production capacity at the Chakan plant by 2.

news.title: Telangana CM to launch Indiramma housing ceremonies by August-end
news.para: Telangana's Chief Minister A Revanth Reddy and Housing Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy are set to launch 'gruhapravesam' ceremonies for newly-built Indiramma houses before the panchayat elections. The Congress government has allocated ₹22,500 crore for Indiramma housing in each constituency, aiming to fulfill the housing dreams of the poor, including Chenchu tribals. The first phase targets completing 4.

news.title: Gurugram: 400 evacuated residents wait as district administration calls for audit by experts
news.para: Following the collapse of a retaining wall at a construction site in Sector 69, Gurugram, hundreds of Neelkanth Enclave residents face prolonged displacement. PWD's initial inspection deemed the damaged buildings unsafe, prompting a comprehensive structural audit by IIT-Delhi or CBRI experts.

news.title: Panvel civic body recovers ₹167 crore property tax in amnesty period
news.para: Panvel City Municipal Corporation recovered ₹167 crore in property tax from over 60,000 property holders. An amnesty scheme provided significant fine exemptions, benefiting thousands. However, a large protest, involving multiple political parties, erupted over the levied property tax, which they claim is excessive and unjustified for a 'D' class municipal corporation.

news.title: DDA to hold phase II of property registration camps in unauthorised colonies on Aug 17
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is set to conduct the second phase of single-window camps on August 17 to facilitate property registration in unauthorized colonies under the PM-UDAY scheme. These camps, organized at ten locations, aim to streamline the process by providing on-the-spot assistance with documentation, registration, and issue resolution.

news.title: MahaRERA to issue warrants to recover ₹90 crore in Palais Royale dispute
news.para: MahaRERA has issued orders for warrants against Honest Shelters. This is to recover about Rs 90 crore in interest. The interest is for delayed possession in the Palais Royale project. IIFL Finance had filed a complaint. The complaint was about non-compliance with a previous order. The order directed Honest Shelters to hand over possession of flats.

news.title: After decade-long ordeal, Bengaluru flat buyers without sale deed win interest payout
news.para: The Karnataka Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (KREAT) has ruled in favor of homebuyers, directing a builder to pay interest on a Rs 34.4 lakh refund. This decision overturns an earlier order by Rera that denied interest despite a nine-year delay in delivering a promised flat.

news.title: Mumbai targets five lakh SRA homes in five years, double its 29-year output
news.para: Mumbai's Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) aims to construct over five lakh homes for slum dwellers in the next five years, more than doubling its 29-year output. Recent reforms, including rule changes, drone surveys, and biometric data collection, have accelerated project delivery.

news.title: After year-long deadlock, Telangana moves to hike property registration values in core urban region
news.para: The Telangana government is set to revise market values for property registration in the core urban region, potentially increasing revenue by ₹2,000-₹2,500 crore annually. Proposed hikes of 30%-50% aim to align official rates with prevailing market prices, especially in high-growth areas. Committees are formed to assess rates, and public feedback will be considered before final implementation.

news.title: Gurugram: No road, Signature Global City-1 buyers protest against developer
news.para: Residents of Signature Global City-1 in Sector 37D, Gurugram, protested against the developer for failing to provide a promised 24-meter-wide road, causing daily commuting challenges. Over 150 families are affected by the missing road, which was a key selling point, and now residents face safety concerns due to poor conditions and lack of emergency access.

news.title: Developers in Pune violating water affidavits to face legal action
news.para: Divisional Commissioner Chandrakant Pulkundwar has directed PMC, PCMC, and PMRDA to file criminal cases against developers failing to honor water affidavits. This directive follows citizen concerns about water scarcity voiced during a meeting with housing society representatives. Local bodies must publish water affidavits online for public scrutiny, and the commissioner expressed displeasure at the absence of key officials.

news.title: Dow Chemical signs 2.5 lakh sq ft office lease at Navi Mumbai's Mindspace Airoli
news.para: Dow Chemicals International has leased 2.56 lakh sq ft of office space in Navi Mumbai's Airoli, marking a significant transaction in the city's IT sector. The 10-year lease, valued at approximately Rs 250 crore, underscores the resilience of Mumbai's commercial office market.

news.title: Elan Group raises ₹140-crore debt
news.para: Elan Group, a Gurugram-based developer, has secured ₹140 crore in debt from BGO and Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC. The company previously raised ₹250 crore from Piramal Finance. Elan Group has also repaid a significant debt of ₹875 crore to Asia Pragati Strategic Investment Fund. These funds were initially invested in 2022 for growth capital.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines Googee Properties for selling plots in unregistered venture
news.para: Telangana RERA has penalized Googee Properties ₹27 lakh for illegally marketing and selling plots in their 'satellite township' without proper registration or approvals. The developer collected advances from buyers under a 'pre-launch offer' for the undeveloped project. RERA has ordered refunds with interest to the complainants and mandated immediate project registration, halting all sales activities until compliance.

news.title: Kerala RERA allows flat-owners to takeover apartments under construction
news.para: K-RERA has made a groundbreaking decision, empowering a flat allottees association to assume control of an unfinished apartment complex in Angamaly. MIR CINTRA's allottees, after the promoter's failure to complete the project despite collecting ₹15.06 crore, can now revive it by pooling funds. This order marks a significant victory for homebuyers in Kerala.

news.title: Yogayatan knocks on NCLT's doors over lenders' decision to allow revised bids for Lavasa
news.para: Yogayatan Group has filed a petition with the NCLT, opposing the lenders' decision to allow revised resolution plans for Lavasa Corp after Yogayatan emerged as the highest bidder. The company fears that Valor Estates' increased bid after the initial offers were opened could compromise the integrity and timeline of the CIRP process.

news.title: Punjab cabinet gives nod to denotify land pooling policy
news.para: The Punjab Cabinet has approved the denotification of the land pooling policy, previously withdrawn due to opposition and court intervention. Amendments to the Punjab Cooperative Societies Act were also approved, removing stamp duty exemptions for certain societies. Additionally, the creation of a 'Panchayat Development Secretary' post and approval for committees overseeing crop procurement and pay commission recommendations were granted.
